Setup and Data Loading

library(dplyr)
library(readr)
library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(knitr)
library(kableExtra)
library(stats)

# Read the data with explicit column types
data <- read_csv("combined_participant_data.csv", 
                 col_types = cols(
                   pid = col_character(),
                   Correct = col_logical(),
                   trialElapsedTime = col_double(),
                   Condition = col_character(),
                   Image = col_character()
                 ))

Separate Dataframes for Problem Types

# Create separate dataframes for each problem type
pretest_data <- data %>% filter(grepl("^P", Image))
congruent_data <- data %>% filter(grepl("^CC", Image))
incongruent_data <- data %>% filter(grepl("^IC", Image))

# Create wide format table for pretest correctness
pretest_correctness <- pretest_data %>%
  mutate(Correct_num = as.numeric(Correct)) %>%
  select(pid, Image, Correct_num, Condition) %>%

    names_sort = TRUE

  mutate(Total_Correct = rowSums(select(., matches("^P.*\\.png$")), na.rm = TRUE))

Filter Participants

# Identify participants with at least 2 correct pretest problems
good_pids <- pretest_correctness %>%
  filter(Total_Correct >= 2) %>%
  pull(pid)

# Update all dataframes
pretest_data <- pretest_data %>% filter(pid %in% good_pids)
congruent_data <- congruent_data %>% filter(pid %in% good_pids)
incongruent_data <- incongruent_data %>% filter(pid %in% good_pids)
data_filtered <- data %>% filter(pid %in% good_pids)

# Save filtered data
write_csv(data_filtered, "combined_participant_data_filtered.csv")

# Update filtered IDs
write_csv(data.frame(pid = good_pids), "participant_ids.csv")

Compare Pretest Correctness Between Conditions

# Calculate mean pretest correctness by participant and condition
pretest_by_condition <- pretest_data %>%
  group_by(pid, Condition) %>%
  summarise(Mean_Correct = mean(as.numeric(Correct)), .groups = 'drop')

# Plot distributions
ggplot(pretest_by_condition, aes(x = Mean_Correct, fill = Condition)) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.5) +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Pretest Correctness by Condition",
       x = "Mean Correctness",
       y = "Density")

# T-test between conditions
t_test_pretest <- t.test(Mean_Correct ~ Condition, data = pretest_by_condition)
wilcox_test_pretest <- wilcox.test(Mean_Correct ~ Condition, data = pretest_by_condition)

# Display results
results_df <- data.frame(
  Test = c("T-test", "Wilcoxon test"),
  Statistic = c(t_test_pretest$statistic, wilcox_test_pretest$statistic),
  P_Value = c(t_test_pretest$p.value, wilcox_test_pretest$p.value)
)

kable(results_df, caption = "Statistical Tests for Pretest Correctness Between Conditions") %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"), 
                full_width = FALSE) %>%
  column_spec(1:3, width = "150px")

Compare Pretest Correctness Between Simplification Groups

# Calculate mean pretest correctness by participant and simplification
pretest_by_simplification <- pretest_data %>%
  group_by(pid, Simplification) %>%
  summarise(Mean_Correct = mean(as.numeric(Correct)), .groups = 'drop')

# Plot distributions
ggplot(pretest_by_simplification,
  aes(x = Mean_Correct, fill = Simplification)) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.5) +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Pretest Correctness by Simplification",
       x = "Mean Correctness",
       y = "Density")

# T-test between simplification groups
t_test_pretest_simp <- t.test(Mean_Correct ~ Simplification, data = pretest_by_simplification)
wilcox_test_pretest_simp <- wilcox.test(Mean_Correct ~ Simplification, data = pretest_by_simplification)

# Display results
results_df <- data.frame(
  Test = c("T-test", "Wilcoxon test"),
  Statistic = c(t_test_pretest_simp$statistic, wilcox_test_pretest_simp$statistic),
  P_Value = c(t_test_pretest_simp$p.value, wilcox_test_pretest_simp$p.value)
)

kable(results_df, caption = "Statistical Tests for Pretest Correctness Between Simplification Groups") %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"), 
                full_width = FALSE) %>%
  column_spec(1:3, width = "150px")

Participant Pretest Response Time Statistics

Calculate Pretest Time Statistics

# Create wide format table for pretest response times
pretest_time <- pretest_data %>%
  select(pid, Image, trialElapsedTime, Condition, Simplification) %>%
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = Image,
    values_from = trialElapsedTime,
    names_sort = TRUE
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    Mean_Time = rowMeans(select(., matches("^P.*\\.png$")), na.rm = TRUE),
    SD_Time = apply(select(., matches("^P.*\\.png$")), 1, sd, na.rm = TRUE),
    Min_Time = apply(select(., matches("^P.*\\.png$")), 1, min, na.rm = TRUE),
    Max_Time = apply(select(., matches("^P.*\\.png$")), 1, max, na.rm = TRUE)
  )

# Display the table
kable(pretest_time, digits = 0, caption = "Pretest Response Times by Participant") %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"), 
                full_width = FALSE) %>%
  column_spec(1:ncol(pretest_time), width = "100px")

# Function to create correctness table
create_correctness_table <- function(data) {
  data %>%
    mutate(Correct_num = as.numeric(Correct)) %>%
    select(pid, Image, Correct_num) %>%
    pivot_wider(
      names_from = Image,
      values_from = Correct_num,
      names_sort = TRUE
    ) %>%
    mutate(Total_Correct = rowSums(select(., -pid), na.rm = TRUE))
}

# Function to create time statistics table
create_time_table <- function(data) {
  data %>%
    select(pid, Image, trialElapsedTime) %>%
    pivot_wider(
      names_from = Image,
      values_from = trialElapsedTime,
      names_sort = TRUE
    ) %>%
    mutate(
      Mean_Time = rowMeans(select(., -pid), na.rm = TRUE),
      SD_Time = apply(select(., -pid), 1, sd, na.rm = TRUE),
      Min_Time = apply(select(., -pid), 1, min, na.rm = TRUE),
      Max_Time = apply(select(., -pid), 1, max, na.rm = TRUE)
    )
}

## Create combined means table
means_table <- bind_rows(
  # Congruent condition
  congruent_time_comparison %>%
    summarise(
      Condition = "Congruent",
      Pretest_Mean = mean(Pretest_Time),
      Pretest_SD = sd(Pretest_Time),
      Condition_Mean = mean(Condition_Time),
      Condition_SD = sd(Condition_Time),
      Difference = mean(Condition_Time - Pretest_Time),
      Cohen_d = (mean(Condition_Time) - mean(Pretest_Time)) / 
                sqrt((sd(Pretest_Time)^2 + sd(Condition_Time)^2) / 2)
    ),
  # Incongruent condition
  incongruent_time_comparison %>%
    summarise(
      Condition = "Incongruent",
      Pretest_Mean = mean(Pretest_Time),
      Pretest_SD = sd(Pretest_Time),
      Condition_Mean = mean(Condition_Time),
      Condition_SD = sd(Condition_Time),
      Difference = mean(Condition_Time - Pretest_Time),
      Cohen_d = (mean(Condition_Time) - mean(Pretest_Time)) / 
                sqrt((sd(Pretest_Time)^2 + sd(Condition_Time)^2) / 2)
    )
)

## Create combined density plot data
density_data <- bind_rows(
  # Pretest data (combined)
  bind_rows(
    congruent_time_comparison %>% 
      select(Time = Pretest_Time) %>%
      mutate(Type = "Pretest"),
    incongruent_time_comparison %>% 
      select(Time = Pretest_Time) %>%
      mutate(Type = "Pretest")
  ),
  # Condition data
  congruent_time_comparison %>% 
    select(Time = Condition_Time) %>%
    mutate(Type = "Congruent"),
  incongruent_time_comparison %>% 
    select(Time = Condition_Time) %>%
    mutate(Type = "Incongruent")
)

# Create density plot
ggplot(density_data, aes(x = Time, fill = Type)) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.5) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Response Times",
       subtitle = "Comparing Pretest and Condition Problems",
       x = "Time (seconds)",
       y = "Density") +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
        legend.title = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) +
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0, max(density_data$Time))) +
  geom_vline(data = density_data %>% 
               group_by(Type) %>% 
               summarise(mean_time = mean(Time)),
             aes(xintercept = mean_time, color = Type),
             linetype = "dashed",
             size = 1) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Set2", guide = "none")

# Prepare data for visualization
all_data <- bind_rows(
  congruent_time_comparison %>% 
    mutate(Condition = "Congruent") %>%
    pivot_longer(cols = c(Pretest_Time, Condition_Time), 
                names_to = "Phase", 
                values_to = "Time"),
  incongruent_time_comparison %>% 
    mutate(Condition = "Incongruent") %>%
    pivot_longer(cols = c(Pretest_Time, Condition_Time), 
                names_to = "Phase", 
                values_to = "Time")
) %>%
  mutate(Phase = factor(Phase, 
                       levels = c("Pretest_Time", "Condition_Time"),
                       labels = c("Pretest Problems", "Condition Problems")))

# Create summary statistics
summary_stats <- all_data %>%
  group_by(Condition, Phase) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_time = mean(Time),
    se_time = sd(Time) / sqrt(n()),
    .groups = 'drop'
  )

# Box plot with points
ggplot(all_data, aes(x = Phase, y = Time, fill = Condition)) +
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.5, outlier.shape = NA) +
  geom_point(position = position_jitterdodge(jitter.width = 0.2), 
             alpha = 0.3, size = 2) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Response Times by Phase and Condition",
       y = "Time (seconds)") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0, hjust = 0.5)) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2")

# Bar plot with error bars
ggplot(summary_stats, aes(x = Phase, y = mean_time, fill = Condition)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge", alpha = 0.7) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_time - se_time, 
                    ymax = mean_time + se_time),
                position = position_dodge(0.9),
                width = 0.2) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Mean Response Times by Phase and Condition",
       subtitle = "Error bars show standard error of the mean",
       y = "Time (seconds)") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0, hjust = 0.5)) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2")
